Philip High School Graduation 2020 Information:

Due to the current restrictions on group size, each graduate was given ten tickets to use for their family to attend Graduation at the Armory. In order for others to show their support, we will be having a parade Saturday, following graduation at approximately 4:00 P.M. The parade will begin at the corner of the First National Bank and Philip Motor, will proceed to Main Street and go West on Pine Street, concluding at the Legion Hall. Please come out to support our 2020 Graduates.

post_text: We wish you the best of recoveries, Ralph and Carol.
shared_text:
Heidi Burns
May 7 at 5:32 PM ·

“A Good Coach Can Change a Race. A Great Coach Can Change a Life.” ❤️
Our hearts go out to these two amazing individuals that have devoted tireless hours to the youth in our communities. Ralph and Carol Kroetch were in a terrible accident last week and we’re so unbelievably grateful they have survived but know they have many days of recovery ahead of them. Please join us in prayers and well wishes for them both. Know that your “kids” are thinking of you daily and will be running for you all summer long. Love to you both!

post_text:
Be the Light Campaign

Members of the Black Hills Conference, including Philip Schools, have decided to become a part of the Be the Light Campaign this Thursday evening to honor numerous groups during this pandemic.

We, the Black Hills Conference, invite you and your community to join us at 8:20 on Thursday, April 16, for 20 minutes by turning on stadium lights. Philip Schools will be participating by turning on the lights at the football field.

Let’s let those who are on the front lines and our seniors know we appreciate them and they are not forgotten.

post_text: Congratulations to the Philip Middle School Acalympics team. They took 3rd place in the Georgia Morse Middle School competition in Pierre out of 14 schools from across South Dakota and Nebraska. This is the 2nd competition they have placed in this year. Way to go Scotties! They will compete again in Kadoka on February 19, and in Philip in March.

post_text:
For those interested in Black Hills Youth Football:

We currently have 10 Mighty Mites (1st/2nd graders), 10 Junior Pee Wee (3rd/4th), and 12 Pee Wee (5th/6th). For us to be able to have a Mighty Mite team we would like to have 12 players, and must have at least 3 people willing to coach the team which would include running practices and games. Currently we have zero coaches or team moms signed up for Mighty Mites.

For us to be able to have a Junior Pee Wee team we will need 16 players, and would like to have one more coach able to help at practices during the week. For us to have a Pee Wee team we would need to get 16 kids signed up to play. We have decided to make Sunday July 14th the cut off for signing up. If you sign your child up for a team that ends up not having enough players or coaches to field a team your money will be refunded.

If we don’t meet these goals by Sunday July 14 we will not be having football this year. You can sign you child up by going the bhyfl.com website.

BHYFL MEETING INFORMATION
There will be a meeting Tuesday May 21st 6:00pm at the Wall High School multipurpose room. We ask that at least one parent of any children planning on playing BHYFL football for the Badlands Eagles attend this meeting. We need to discuss the upcoming season and whether or not we will have the resources to continue to have teams at all three divisions this year and going forward. We look forward to seeing everyone there and appreciate everyone taking the time to attend this meeting. Please pass this along to anyone who might be interested in playing. Eligible players are anyone that will be in grades 1-6 in the 2019-2020 school year.

post_text: Philip is lucky to have such wonderful alumni!!! A big thanks goes out to Gaylord “Guy” Paulson of the class of 1955 for creating a mosaic for the new school. The mosaic is hanging outside of the new cafeteria. Guy is shown with his wife (next to him in white in the group picture) and other members of the class of 1955. Gavin Brucklacher, another alumni, also helped by making the wooden plaque for the engraved plate. Thank you to Brigitte Brucklacher for the photos.

CONGRATULATIONS!!!!!!!
It is official! Dyson and Hunter placed 6th in the National Capitol Hill Stock Market Game they participated in during Personal Finance. Mrs. Brucklacher will be travelling with them to Washington, D.C. June 12-14. This is rather equivalent to hitting a jackpot in Deadwood.....they edged out 3374 other high school teams in the nation. Many of the school were "academies" or prep schools. It was a lot of luck with a small part of skill! If you need a good stock, ask the boys what worked for them!

Mondays - 6:30 A.M. - 8:00 A.M.
Tuesdays - 6:30 A.M. - 8:00 A.M. Thursdays - 6:30 A.M. - 8:00 A.M.
Thursdays - 5:00 P.M. - 6:00 P.M.

If you would be able to commit to any of these times for the months of June and July, please let me know. If you would like to be a fill in when needed, please feel free to call me at the school with your name and number and I will put you on our list.

Thank you,
Mrs. Menzel
